<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1100" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1100">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Woodford</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-16"><hi rend="italic">April 16,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 226.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am this morning in receipt of telegram
                            from Mr. Bartleman, United States consul at Malaga, Spain, stating that
                            his residence was stoned last evening. I have at once asked the Spanish
                            Government to protect all United States consuls and consular offices
                            throughout Spain.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stewart L. Woodford</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>